radiographic_examinations.findings: Normal mediastinum without pulmonary edema, cardiomegaly, or air-space disease.
100% occlusion of the left anterior descending artery; left main, left circumflex, and right coronary arteries did not have clinically significant disease.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: The percutaneous intervention restored blood flow (TIMI grade 3), which was successful.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Ejection fraction of 40%, with hypokinesis of the apex, the middle and distal anterior wall, and the middle and distal anterior septum.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: At the 6-month follow-up visit, the ejection fraction improved to 50%.
